# Privacy Policy for Worklog App

Effective Date: September 21, 2025  

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how the **Worklog App** (‚Äúwe,‚Äù ‚Äúour,‚Äù or ‚Äúus‚Äù) handles your information.

## Information We Collect
- **User-entered data**: Hours worked, overtime, pay rates, allowances, and related work-log information.  
- **Device information**: Basic diagnostic info (app version, crash reports via Firebase Crashlytics).  

We **do not** collect sensitive personal data such as contacts, messages, photos, or precise location.

## How We Use Information
- To calculate and display wages, overtime, and work summaries.  
- To store preferences locally on your device (e.g., currency, date format).  
- To improve app stability and fix bugs (anonymous crash reports).  

## Data Storage
- All work-log data is stored **locally on your device**.  
- Crash reports are handled by **Firebase Crashlytics** and may include anonymized technical info.  

We do not share or sell your data.

## Purchases
- Payments and subscriptions are handled securely through **Google Play Billing**.  
- We do not store your payment information.  

## Your Choices
- You can clear all app data at any time by uninstalling the app.  
- You may also manage purchase history and subscriptions via the Google Play Store.  

